    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-02-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-02-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received April
                        25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 135.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that on yesterday
                    I received from Rear-Admiral McCann a telegram requesting that I would notify
                    the Department of the Navy of his arrival at Talcahuano. I accordingly cabled as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="flushleft">To <hi rend="smallcaps">Blaine</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pensacola</hi> arrived Talcahuano 20th. Admiral McCann
                            desires inform Secretary Navy. Some fighting Iquique. Remainder country
                            tranquil. <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patrick Egan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
